.SH NAME
squirrel \- command-line tools for squirrel neuroimaging data packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B squirrel
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ arguments ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B squirrel
creates, inspects, and modifies
.B squirrel
data packages
.RI ( .sqrl
files). A squirrel package is a self-contained archive that stores
neuroimaging and associated data \(em subjects, studies, imaging series,
analyses, pipelines, observations, interventions, experiments, and data
dictionaries \(em together with a JSON manifest.
.PP
The following commands are available:
.TP
.B dicom2squirrel
Convert a DICOM directory into a squirrel package.
.TP
.B bids2squirrel
Convert a BIDS directory into a squirrel package.
.TP
.B info
Display information about a package or its contents.
.TP
.B modify
Add, remove, or update objects within a package.
.TP
.B extract
Extract objects from a package to disk.
.TP
.B validate
Check whether a package is valid and readable.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS dicom2squirrel
Convert a directory of DICOM files into a squirrel package.
.PP
.B squirrel dicom2squirrel
.I dicomdirectory package
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B Arguments
.RS 4
.TP
.I dicomdirectory
Path to the input directory containing DICOM files.
.TP
.I package
Path to the output squirrel package
.RI ( .sqrl
extension added if omitted).
.RE
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress header and progress output.
.TP
.BI \-\-dataformat " format"
Output data format. Default:
.BR nifti4dgz .
Possible values:
.BR anon " (anonymized DICOM),"
.BR nifti4d ","
.BR nifti4dgz ","
.BR nifti3d ","
.BR nifti3dgz ","
.BR orig " (unmodified DICOM)."
.TP
.BI \-\-dirformat " format"
Directory naming within the package.
.B orig
uses original subject IDs (default);
.B seq
uses sequential numbers.
.RE
.PP
.B Examples
.RS 4
.EX
squirrel dicom2squirrel /data/dicoms /output/study.sqrl
squirrel dicom2squirrel /data/dicoms /output/study.sqrl \\
    --dataformat nifti4d --dirformat orig
.EE
.RE
.SS bids2squirrel
Convert a BIDS-formatted directory into a squirrel package.
.PP
.B squirrel bids2squirrel
.I bidsdirectory package
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B Arguments
.RS 4
.TP
.I bidsdirectory
Path to the root BIDS directory.
.TP
.I package
Path to the output squirrel package.
.RE
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress header and progress output.
.TP
.B \-\-overwrite
Overwrite an existing package at the output path.
.TP
.B \-\-debugsql
Log all SQL statements (for troubleshooting).
.RE
.PP
.B Examples
.RS 4
.EX
squirrel bids2squirrel /data/bids_study /output/study.sqrl
squirrel bids2squirrel /data/bids_study /output/study.sqrl --overwrite
.EE
.RE
.SS info
Display information about a package or its contents.
.PP
.B squirrel info
.I package
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.BI \-\-object " type"
Object type to display. Default:
.BR package .
Possible values:
.BR all ", " package ", " subject ", " study ", " series ", " observation ", "
.BR intervention ", " experiment ", " pipeline ", " groupanalysis ", " datadictionary .
.TP
.BI \-\-subjectid " id"
Filter by subject ID.
.TP
.BI \-\-studynum " num"
Filter by study number. Requires
.BR \-\-subjectid .
.TP
.BI \-\-dataset " type"
Amount of detail:
.BR id ", " basic ", or " full .
Default:
.BR full .
.TP
.BI \-\-format " format"
Output format:
.B list
or
.BR csv .
Default:
.BR csv .
.RE
.PP
.B Examples
.RS 4
.EX
squirrel info study.sqrl
squirrel info study.sqrl --object subject --dataset full --format csv
squirrel info study.sqrl --object study --subjectid S1234
squirrel info study.sqrl --object series --subjectid S1234 --studynum 1
.EE
.RE
.SS modify
Add, remove, update, or otherwise transform objects within an existing package.
.PP
.B squirrel modify
.I package
.B \-\-operation
.I op
.B \-\-object
.I type
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress header and progress output.
.TP
.BI \-\-operation " op"
Operation to perform. Possible values:
.BR add ", " remove ", " update ", " splitbymodality ", " removephi ", " renumber .
.TP
.BI \-\-object " type"
Object type to operate on. Possible values:
.BR package ", " subject ", " study ", " series ", " analysis ", "
.BR intervention ", " observation ", " experiment ", " pipeline ", "
.BR groupanalysis ", " datadictionary .
.TP
.BI \-\-datapath " path"
Path to data for the new object. Wildcards supported
(e.g.\&
.IR /path/*.dcm ).
.TP
.BI \-\-objectid " id"
ID, name, or number of the existing object to modify or remove.
.TP
.BI \-\-subjectid " id"
Parent subject ID. Required when adding or removing a study, series,
observation, intervention, or analysis.
.TP
.BI \-\-studynum " num"
Parent study number. Required when adding or removing a series or analysis
.RB ( \-\-subjectid
also required).
.TP
.BI \-\-seriesnum " num"
Parent series number. Required when updating a series
.RB ( \-\-subjectid
and
.B \-\-studynum
also required).
.TP
.BI \-\-objectdata " string"
URL-encoded
.IR key = value
string specifying object metadata, pairs joined by
.BR & .
Use
.B \-\-variablelist
to see valid keys for each object type.
.TP
.BI \-\-variablelist " type"
Print all settable variable names for the given object type and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-digits " num"
Number of digits in the renumbered subject ID (e.g.\&
.B 4
produces
.BR 0001 \(en 9999 ).
Default: auto-sized to fit the largest generated number.
Used with
.BR renumber .
.TP
.BI \-\-startnum " num"
Starting number for renumbering. Default:
.BR 1 .
Used with
.BR renumber .
.TP
.BI \-\-prefix " string"
Prefix prepended to renumbered subject IDs (e.g.\&
.B sub
produces
.BR sub0001 ", " sub0002 ", " \&... ).
Used with
.BR renumber .
.TP
.B \-\-random
Randomly assign new IDs instead of sorting subjects ascending before
renumbering. Used with
.BR renumber .
.RE
.PP
.B Examples
.RS 4
.EX
squirrel modify study.sqrl --operation update --object subject \\
    --objectid S1234 --objectdata 'DateOfBirth=1999-12-31&Sex=M'

squirrel modify study.sqrl --operation add --object subject \\
    --objectdata 'SubjectID=S9999&Sex=F&DateOfBirth=1985-06-15'

squirrel modify study.sqrl --operation remove --object series \\
    --subjectid S1234 --studynum 1 --objectid 3

squirrel modify study.sqrl --operation splitbymodality

squirrel modify study.sqrl --operation removephi

squirrel modify study.sqrl --operation renumber

squirrel modify study.sqrl --operation renumber \\
    --digits 4 --startnum 1001 --prefix sub

squirrel modify study.sqrl --operation renumber --random

squirrel modify study.sqrl --variablelist study
.EE
.RE
.SS extract
Extract one or more objects from a package to a directory on disk.
.PP
.B squirrel extract
.I package
.B \-\-object
.I type
.B \-\-objectid
.I id
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B Options
.RS 4
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress header and progress output.
.TP
.BI \-\-object " type"
Object type to extract. Possible values:
.BR subject ", " study ", " series ", " analysis ", " experiment ", "
.BR pipeline ", " groupanalysis ", " datadictionary .
.TP
.BI \-\-outdir " path"
Destination directory for extracted files.
.TP
.BI \-\-objectid " id"
ID, name, or number of the object to extract.
.TP
.BI \-\-subjectid " id"
Parent subject ID. Required when extracting a study, series, or analysis.
.TP
.BI \-\-studynum " num"
Parent study number. Required when extracting a series or analysis
.RB ( \-\-subjectid
also required).
.RE
.PP
.B Examples
.RS 4
.EX
squirrel extract study.sqrl --object subject \\
    --objectid S1234ABC --outdir /tmp/out

squirrel extract study.sqrl --object series --objectid 1 \\
    --subjectid S1234ABC --studynum 1 --outdir /tmp/out

squirrel extract study.sqrl --object experiment \\
    --objectid MyExperiment --outdir /tmp/out
.EE
.RE
.SS validate
Check whether a squirrel package is readable and structurally valid.
.PP
.B squirrel validate
.I package
.PP
.B Examples
.RS 4
.EX
squirrel validate study.sqrl
.EE
.RE
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help text for the current command and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information and exit.
.SH OBJECT HIERARCHY
A squirrel package organizes data in the following hierarchy:
.PP
.EX
package
\(lc\(em subject
\(uc    \(lc\(em study
\(uc    \(uc    \(lc\(em series
\(uc    \(uc    \(lq\(em analysis
\(uc    \(lc\(em observation
\(uc    \(lq\(em intervention
\(lc\(em experiment
\(lc\(em pipeline
\(lc\(em group-analysis
\(lq\(em data-dictionary
.EE
